title: 2010.11.07-F1.18.Brazil.Race.BBC1_UK [TDMK1]
description:
2010.11.07-F1.18.Brazil.Race.BBC1_UK-TDMK1.m4v

Jake Humphrey introduces coverage of the 18th and penultimate round of the season at Interlagos in Sao Paulo (Start-time 4.00pm). Spain's Fernando Alonso goes into this race with an 11-point lead in the drivers' championship following his win at the rain-affected Korean Grand Prix last time out, which also saw Red Bull's Mark Webber and Sebastian Vettel fail to finish. Australian Webber won this race last year, but Jenson Button stole the headlines when his fifth-placed finish, after starting in 14th position on the grid, was enough for him to claim the 2009 World Championship with one race remaining. With commentary by Jonathan Legard and Martin Brundle, and analysis by Eddie Jordan and David Coulthard.

Now encoded as 'MP4 All Play'... As a departure from the DivX files which I have uploaded in the past, I've made the decision to get with the 21st century & start encoding with the following specs this year;

MP4 - 640x352 - 800Kb/s H264 Video - 44.1KHz/128Kbps Stereo AAC Audio

My belief is this is the best all round setup, and hopefully you will agree!

This video will play on a computer with VLC, XBMC, XBox360, PS3, iPad all iPhones - enjoy the show... :)
